Package synchronizer

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Synchronizer
    A common interface for both central and personal synchronizers.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    CentralSynchronization
    A class serving as the interface for the package of classes responsible for central synchronization; also this class assumes responsibility over the creation of instances of al classes of the package needed at startup time.
    CentralSynchronizer
    A class for objects synchronizing all agents in the system.
    DistributedSynchronization
    A class serving as the interface for the package dealing with distributed synchronization.
    DummySynchronizer  
    FileDistributedSynchronization
    A class responsible for the creation of instances of all classes of this package needed at startup time when distributed synchronization is used.
    NoSynchronization  
    PersonalSynchronizer  
    SyncElement
    A class for members of syncsets.
    Synchronization
    An abstract superclass for interfaces of the synchronizer-package.
